        {
            "title": "Bitcoin and Ethereum weakened amid geopolitical tensions, while XRP and Dogecoin gained. Bitcoin at $92,635.81, Ethereum at $3,182.04, XRP at $1.97, Solana at $133.58, and Dogecoin at $0.1283. Bitcoin consolidating between $92,000-$93,300, trading volume up 10% in last 24 hours. $100 million liquidated in derivatives market in last 24 hours. Bitcoin's open interest rose by 0.73%. \"Fear\" sentiment prevails according to Crypto Fear & Greed Index.",
            "id": "9d59d8d4-d196-4442-82ae-e4b4bdd37d50",
            "description": "Leading cryptocurrencies experienced a lackluster performance on Monday due to geopolitical tensions over Greenland. Bitcoin saw a minimal decrease of -0.12% to $92,635.81, while Ethereum dropped by -1.06% to $3,182.04. XRP increased by +1.33% to $1.97, Solana fell by -0.38% to $133.58, and Dogecoin rose by +1.01% to $0.1283. Bitcoin consolidated between $92,000 to $93,300 with a 10% rise in trading volume. Ethereum hit a low of $3,166 after trading sideways. Over $100 million was liquidated from the derivatives market in the last 24 hours. Bitcoin's open interest increased by 0.73% and the percentage of Binance traders with long BTC positions rose to 67%. The Crypto Fear & Greed Index reflected a prevailing \"Fear\" sentiment in the market.",
